    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-08-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Choate reports that Lord Lansdowne desires to know the views of the United
                    States Government on the sinking of the <hi rend="italic">Knight Commander</hi>
                    and the depredations of the volunteer fleet on neutrals, and generally
                    concerning the dealings of belligerents with neutrals to enforce the right of
                    search for contraband.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
